==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fantasia
<hw>Fan*ta"si*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. See
<er>Fancy</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A continuous composition,
not divided into what are called movements, or governed by the ordinary
rules of musical design, but in which the author's fancy roves
unrestricted by set form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fantasied</ent>⟦br⟧
